At least 36 people have been killed in a bus crash in Veracruz, southern Mexico, local authorities report.

A passenger bus slammed into a broken-down truck and burst into flames shortly after midnight in the southeastern Mexican state.

The victims were local businessmen and women, reportedly shopkeepers, who were travelling from the Tabasco state capital of Villahermosa to Mexico City, the state civil defense agency said.

