Federal police concluded that the truck was badly parked, the state government said.

Via Twitter, Mexican President Enrique Pena Nieto sent a message of condolences to the families of those who died.

The tragedy was a dark start to the Palm Sunday, celebrated as the start of Easter in the predominantly Roman Catholic country.

Bus crashes and road accidents occur frequently in Mexico, taking a heavy death toll each year.

In 2012, at least 43 people died when a truck hit a bus in Veracruz, and just a couple of months later more than 30 others were killed in a separate accident in Guerrero state.

